/*S*/ Kurzbeschreibung
@NODE "Kurzbeschreibung" "Felix-Anleitung / Kurzbeschreibung"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}1. Shortdescription @{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}@{FG FILL}@{apen 11}@{b}Felix.api is a PlugIn for the "GoldED" text editor.@{ub}@{apen 1}@{FG TEXT}

@{par}@{u}Features@{uu}:11
@{par}ｷ Freeware
@{par}ｷ checks if files have been changed by other tasks in the background and reloads them if you want.
@{par}ｷ Provides an ARexx-command to show a list of all currently open GoldED-text-windows.
@{par}ｷ locale.library-support
@{par}ｷ Fontsensitive
@{par}
@{par}The complete source-code (for StormC 3.0) is included.
@{par}
@{par}The name Felix is an abbreviation for the german word "Fensterliste" witch just means "windowlist".

@{par}@{u}History@{uu}:
@{par}@{b}39.2@{ub}: Initial releases
@{par}@{b}39.3@{ub}: Matthias Henze (stormamiga.lib) fixed the startup code of Felix.
@{par}
@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Installation
@node "Installation" "Felix-Anleitung / Installation"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}2. Installation@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}The installation of that PlugIn is so damn simple, that I didn't wrote a skript for that.
Just click here to @{"Install" SYSTEM "execute /install/install.english.bat"}.

@endnode
/*E*/
/*S*/ Requirements
@NODE "Voraussetzungen" "Felix-Anleitung / Voraussetzungen"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}4. Requirements for the Felix.api.@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}To use the Felix.api you will need GoldED of course.
@{par}OS 3.0 is also required.

@{par}To compile the included sources you need the StormC-compiler.

@{par}@{b}Important notes about the sources:@{ub}
@{par}Some of the sources include the file "GOLDED:developer/api/include/api.h" (release 7).
That include-file includes some other files. One of these files is the "exec/lists.h".
which is unnessecarily includes twice.
I think that one of them originally should be "exec/libraries.h" because during
compiling the compiler claims at serval points that the "struct Library" is unknown.
Please correct that by editing the api.h-file, with Gold-ED of course :-)
After that you should be able to compile the project without any errors.

@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Beschreibung
@NODE "Beschreibung" "Felix-Anleitung / Beschreibung"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}3. Usage@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}After installing the Felix.api you can activate it using the API-section of the
GoldED-settings (the one with the Plug-symbol).

@{par}After that you won't see any changes. But, if a text-file wich is opened in GoldED,
has been changed in the background and you press a key in the GoldED-window, a requester
appears that informs you about that. An alternative way to check the accesses is to use
the ARexx-command "@{u}CHECKACCESSES@{uu}". An ARexx-skript that checks the accesses
every 5 seconds could look like that:

@{par}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}/* felixdemo.rexx - checks fileaccesses every 5 seconds */
@{par}do forever
@{par}    ADDRESS "GOLDED.1"
@{par}    CHECKACCESSES
@{par}    ADDRESS COMMAND
@{par}    WAIT 5
@{par}end@{FG TEXT}

@{par}The ARexx-command "@{u}FELIX@{uu}" is just an "About"-command, that opens
a requester that informs you about the Felix.api.

@{par}The most important command is the ARexx-command "@{u}WINDOWLIST@{uu}".
This command opens a window with a list of all currently open text-windows.
The synopsis is as following:

@{par}WINDOWLIST X/N Y/N ENTRIES/N KEEPPOSITION/S OFF/S

@{par}With the parameters X and Y you can set the position of the window.
A value of -1 means that the window will be centered on the screen.

@{par}ENTRIES is the number of entries in the list you can see without scrolling, just means
the height of the window.

@{par}KEEPPOSITION can be used if you want Felix.api to remembers the last
windowposition on opening the time.

@{par}OFF is to close the window via ARexx-command.

@{par}@{b}How to use the window:@{ub}
@{par}The window contains the list of open text-window itself and the gadgets "@{u}O@{uu}kay",
"@{u}C@{uu}lose" and "C@{u}a@{uu}ncel".
In the list the current text-window is selected.

@{par}Pressing the "@{u}Okay@{uu}"-gadget the window that is selected in the list
will pop to front and the Felix-window disappears.

@{par}Pressing the "@{u}Close@{uu}"-gadget the window that is selected in the list
will be closed just as you would click the close-gadget of the window.

@{par}And the "@{u}Cancel@{uu}"-gadget will close the Felix-window.

@{par}Doubleclicking an entry in the list the corresponding text-window pops to front
without closing the Felix-window.

@{par}The @{u}Return-Key@{uu} does the same as the "Okay"-gadget
@{par}The @{u}ESC-Key@{uu} does the same as "Cancel"-gadget.
@{par}The @{u}Spacebar@{uu} is like a dobble-click on the selected entry.


@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ Known bugs
@NODE "BekannteFehler" "Felix-Anleitung / Known Bugs"
@{bpen 4}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}@{b}4. Known Felix.api bugs@{ub}@{FG TEXT}@{bpen 0}

@{par}While testing felix.api we discovered a bug on an Amiga 1200, which made the
automatically updating the text-windows not work. The system doesn't crash,
but it just does nothing. The windowlist-feature works alright.
If anyone can fix the bug with the included source-code, it would be nice
to inform me about that and how I can fix it too.

@ENDNODE
